# Cisco Packet Tracer - Console Connectivity Lab

In this lab, I learned how to access Cisco devices using console connectivity in Cisco Packet Tracer.

## What I Did

* Connected a PC to a Cisco 2960 switch using a console cable
* Accessed the Cisco IOS CLI using Terminal
* Explored User EXEC and Privileged EXEC modes
* Used basic commands like:

  * show version
  * show clock
  * enable
  * clock set
* Connected a laptop to a Cisco ISR4321 router using a mini-USB console cable
* Accessed the router CLI through terminal emulation

## Devices Used

* Cisco 2960 Switch
* Cisco ISR4321 Router
* PC
* Laptop
* Console Cable
* Mini-USB Cable

## Commands Used

show version
show clock
enable
clock set 15:28:00 Nov 11 2020
end

## What I Learned

* Basic Cisco IOS navigation
* Console connectivity
* Difference between User EXEC and Privileged EXEC mode
* Basic switch and router configuration
* Terminal access using serial and USB console connections

## Security Note

Unauthorized access can be prevented by:

* Setting console passwords
* Using login authentication
* Restricting physical access to devices

